# Sticky Sessions
A WebSocket connection must remain on the same server after it's established.

Client
↓
Load Balancer
↓
Server 5

Connection stays here, If the load balancer moves packets to another server:

Server :- I don't know this connection. That's why WebSocket deployments typically use sticky sessions (or consistent routing) for the lifetime of the connection.

Advantages
Real-time communication
Very low latency
Bi-directional messaging
Less network overhead
Reduced bandwidth compared to polling
Better user experience

Disadvantages
 Oen connections consume server memory.
 Harder to scale than stateless HTTP APIs.
 Load balancing requires connection-aware routing.
 Idle connections need heartbeat (Ping/Pong) management.
 Not ideal for simple request-response APIs.

